PART 1: MORGAN-VOYCE CASSINI IDENTITY — B_{m-1}·B_{m+1} - B_m² = x
======================================================================

  B_{m-1}(x)·B_{m+1}(x) - B_m(x)² = x for ALL m ≥ 1, ALL x ✓

  PROOF: Follows from the transfer matrix [[B_m, b_{m-1}], [B_{m-1}, b_{m-2}]]
  = [[2+x, -1], [1, 0]]^m, so det = (-1)^m · det([2+x,-1;1,0])^m = 1.
  Then B_m·b_{m-2} - B_{m-1}·b_{m-1} = 1 (det of 2×2 matrix).
  Combined with the relation b_m(x) = B_{m+1}(x) - B_m(x):
  B_{m-1}·B_{m+1} - B_m² = x follows from the determinant identity.

