======================================================================
PART 4: prod(Q_k) = 1 — THE UNIT PRODUCT
======================================================================

B_m(0) = C(m+0, 0) = 1 for all m
prod(Q_k) = B_m(0) = 1 — proved algebraically!

  p= 5, m= 2: prod(Q_k) = 1.0000000000
  p= 7, m= 3: prod(Q_k) = 1.0000000000
  p=11, m= 5: prod(Q_k) = 1.0000000000
  p=13, m= 6: prod(Q_k) = 1.0000000000
  p=17, m= 8: prod(Q_k) = 1.0000000000
  p=29, m=14: prod(Q_k) = 1.0000000000
  p=41, m=20: prod(Q_k) = 1.0000000000

Geometric mean = prod(Q_k)^{1/m} = 1
Arithmetic mean = sum(Q_k)/m = m(m+1)/(2m) = (m+1)/2
AM/GM = (m+1)/2 → ∞ as m → ∞
This shows the Q_k are VERY non-uniform (far from equal).

