======================================================================
GRAND SYNTHESIS — FIBONACCI-LATTICE-GAS-TOURNAMENT
======================================================================

PROVEN IDENTITIES FOR INTERVAL TOURNAMENT:
  1. prod(Q_k) = 1  (unit product, from B_m(0) = 1)
  2. prod(1+Q_k) = F_p  (Fibonacci, from B_m(1) = F_{2m+1})
  3. prod(a+Q_k) = a^m B_m(1/a)  (parametric, Morgan-Voyce)
  4. B_{m-1}B_{m+1} - B_m² = x  (Cassini-MV identity)
  5. disc(Q) = V(Q)² = p^{m-1}  (cyclotomic discriminant)

CONJECTURED:
  6. H ≥ p · F_p  for all circulant tournaments
     (Verified at p=5,7,11,13 — always min(H) >> F_p)

LATTICE GAS BRIDGE:
  7. H = I(Ω(T), 2)  — hard-core gas on odd-cycle graph, activity 2
  8. prod(1+Q_k) = I(∅_m, Q)  — no-exclusion gas, non-uniform activities Q_k
  9. I(Ω, z) / prod(z+Q) measures the graph constraint effect
     At p=5: this ratio is ~1.18 at z=2 but EXACTLY 1 at z=3!

THE SPECTRAL CONCENTRATION MECHANISM:
  10. Interval has maximal Q_1 / Σ Q_k → 2/3 (most concentrated)
  11. prod(Q_k) = 1 forces: if Q_1 is large, other Q_k must be small
  12. This concentration → max additive energy → max H (for p ≥ 13)
  13. The golden ratio φ² appears as B_m/B_{m-1} → φ² (limit of ratios)

